molecular constants for SiC in the two electronic states. The
principal equilibrium molecular constants for the A3{$Sigma-$} state
are: Be=0.6181195(18)cm-1, {$alpha$}e=0.0051921(20)cm-1,
re=1.8020884(26)AA, and Te=3773.31(17)cm-1, with one standard
deviation given in parentheses. The effect of a perturbation was
recognized between the {$nu$}=4 level of X3{$Pi$} and the {$nu$}=0
level of A3{$Sigma$}, and the analysis was carried out to determine
the interaction parameter between the two states.},
author = {Deo, M. N. and Kawaguchi, K.},
doi = {10.1016/j.jms.2004.06.016},
journal = {Journal of Molecular Spectroscopy},
pages = {76--82},
title = {{Infrared Emission Studies of the {{A3$\Sigma$}}-\textendash{{X3$\Pi$}} Electronic Transition of the {{SiC}} Radical}},
volume = {228},
year = {2004}
}

@article{03MiDaxx.SiC,
abstract = {Spectroscopic constants and molecular properties of monocarbides AlC
and SiC have been studied in their ground state using hybrid HF/DF
B3LYP method. The effect of basis set on the spectroscopic constants
and molecular properties has been discussed. The consistency of the
calculated values of spectroscopic constants and molecular properties
such as electron affinity, ionization potential and dipole moment has
been obtained using four different basis sets with improved quality.
The spectroscopic constants of AlC and SiC agree well with the
existing experimental and theoretical values wherever available. The
molecular properties of AlC and SiC are reported for the first time.},
author = {Midda, S. and Das, A. K.},
doi = {10.1016/S0166-1280(03)00327-0},
journal = {Journal of Molecular Structure: THEOCHEM},
pages = {67--71},
title = {{Spectroscopic Constants and Molecular Properties of {{AlC}} and {{SiC}} in Their Ground State}},
volume = {633},
year = {2003}
}

@article{98CoElxx.SiC,
abstract = {Several bands of the Chphantom{,}3{$Pi$}textendash Xhphantom{,}3{$Pi$}
and Chphantom{,}3{$Pi$}textendash Ahphantom{,}3{$Sigma-$} systems of
SiC were recorded on photographic plates in the 350textendash 560 nm
visible region from an electric glow discharge with a composite SiC/Cu
cathode and a 1000 gauss transverse magnetic field. The present work
extends observation of the Chphantom{,}3{$Pi$}textendash
Xhphantom{,}3{$Pi$} transition previously made in supersonic jet to
higher J-line values and to the 3{$Pi$}0textendash 3{$Pi$}0 component.
It proved impossible to record these spectra when using Fourier
transform spectroscopy. A discussion is given to explain tentatively
the reasons for this failure.},
author = {Cossart, Daniel and Elhanine, Mohammed},
doi = {10.1016/S0009-2614(97)01451-6},
